caption>A set of <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Romal" title=
=3D"Romal">romal</a></i> reins, featuring a quirt at the end of the <i>roma=
l</i></figcaption></figure>
<p>A <b>whip</b> is a blunt weapon or implement used in a striking motion t=
o create sound or pain. Whips can be used for <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Flagellation" title=3D"Flagellation">flagellation</a> against h=
umans or animals to exert control through <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Pain_compliance" title=3D"Pain compliance">pain compliance</a> or f=
ear of pain, or be used as an audible cue through the distinct <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whipcrack" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Whip=
crack">whipcrack</a> effect. Whips are commonly used on horses to give subt=
le cues as tapping. The portion used for striking is generally either a fir=
m rod designed for direct contact, or a flexible line requiring a specializ=
ed swing. The former is easier and more precise, the latter offers longer r=
each and greater force. Some varieties, such as a hunting whip or lunge whi=
p, have an extended stock section in addition to the line.
</p><p>Whips such as the "<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cat_o%27=
_nine_tails" title=3D"Cat o' nine tails">cat o' nine tails</a>" and <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Knout" title=3D"Knout">knout</a> are spec=
ifically developed for <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Corporal_pu=
nishment" title=3D"Corporal punishment">corporal punishment</a> or <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Torture" title=3D"Torture">torture</a> on=
 human targets. Certain religious practices and <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/BDSM" title=3D"BDSM">BDSM</a> activities involve the self-use=
 of whips or the use of whips between consenting partners. Misuse on animal=
s may be considered <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Animal_cruelty=
" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Animal cruelty">animal cruelty</a>, and mi=
suse on humans may be viewed as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/As=
sault" title=3D"Assault">assault</a>.
</p>
